---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

// Update this date when you revise the page (convention from nownownow.com).
const updated = 'June 2026';
---
<Base title="Now — Bradley Davis" current="now" description="What Bradley Davis is working on right now.">
  <h1>Now</h1>
  <p class="muted sans">Updated {updated}.</p>

  <p>
    I left OKX in May 2026 after four years building its fiat payments platform.
    Right now I am figuring out what is next and using the gap to build in the
    open rather than just interview.
  </p>

  <p>The current focus:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Going deep on agentic engineering: MCP servers in daily use, multi-agent
      orchestration, and the patterns that actually hold up outside a demo.
    </li>
    <li>
      Running everything off a five-machine, Nix-managed homelab (a Bitcoin and
      Lightning node, Pi-hole DNS, Home Assistant, ZFS replication) as a daily
      proving ground.
    </li>
    <li>
      Starting to write some of it down. Posts are in the works on running MCP
      servers in daily use and on the Nix control plane behind the homelab.
    </li>
    <li>
      Off the keyboard: two small kids, a new house, and a front yard I am slowly
      bringing back from the dead.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p class="muted">
    Want to talk shop or about a role? <a href="mailto:hire@bdavis.ai">hire@bdavis.ai</a>.
  </p>

  <p class="muted sans" style="font-size:0.85rem;">
    This is a <a href="https://nownownow.com/about">now page</a>.
  </p>
</Base>
